('Correctiva', 460, 'EN: Photos sent by the client are reviewed, the date claimed is June 24. In this sale 5 production dates were uploaded, the claim is about a single production date.\r\nRecords of that production date are reviewed (GMP - pH control), no deviations are found that could explain   the dark color of the claimed product. \r\nThe production is carried out with hind quarters which pH have been checked (<5.8) immediatly after the sanitary maturation process and prior to carcass quartering and deboning. The quarters rejected by pH are destined for local market.\r\nES: Se revisan fotos que envía el cliente, donde se visualiza el desvío de color que éste reclama.\r\nLa fecha reclamada es el 24 de Junio . Las fechas cargadas fueron 11/05-21/06-22/06-23/06 y 24/06, hay reclamo de producto de una sola fecha de produccion.\r\nSe revisan registros asociados a la fecha de produccion ( GMP - control de pH ) no encontrándose desvíos que puedan explicar el color oscuro del producto reclamado.\r\nToda la produccion de cortes traseros se realiza con cuartos con control de  pH < 5,8 luego de finalizado el proceso de maduracion sanitaria y previo al cuarteo / ingreso desosado, siendo todos los cuartos rechazados por pH destinados al abasto local.', 'EN:with reference to container in attachment, pls note that we have received a claim from the customer whom we sold the whole lot to. \r\nHe found 1547kg topsides -5% tolerance Kg. 1246 =  kg. 301 dark topsides (so out of PH control) out of the tolerance \r\n We do include herewith the pictures as well for you to have all the details necessary. \r\n The customer kept these topsides at a lower price (Euro 3.20) which in USD with today’s rate (1.1593) is USD 3.71.  \r\nWe ask you therefore for a credit note of USD 1116.71 (kg. 301 x usd 3.71/kg) since we must credit this difference to the customer as goods show clearly quality problems. \r\n Thanks for your feedback and confirmation back to us.', 'Bervini', 3, '2021-11-01', ''